Got the full official VESC interface manual. Here's exactly what it says:

**Flash the firmware:** Since the release 5.03 dev 51, the VESC firmware includes all necessary commands to be driven by OpenFFBoard. Download from: https://github.com/manoukianv/vescFirmware4OpenFFBoard/releases — upgrade the firmware with VESC Tool connected via USB. **NEVER turn on a VESC without a motor wired — you will burn the VESC.**

**The full confirmed VESC setup sequence:**

1. Wire VESC, motor and encoder — ALL before powering on
2. Start VESC Tool to setup
3. Motor setup in FOC, select encoder and resolution
4. Setup current for motor/battery — don't change abs max current. Motor current = max current for FFB
5. In FOC tab do motor calibration, choose ENCODER not SENSORLESS, save
6. In FOC/Encoder tab do calibration, save
7. In RT/graph go to position tab, click encoder and turn shaft — graph must move
8. In general/motor/advanced change min current to 0.0A and frequency to 25000hz
9. Test dutycycle — motor must turn CW. If not reverse motor and redo sensor calibration
10. Test torque force — force must be linear during a turn. If not you have FOC calibration issue

**OpenFFBoard side:**
In the Configurator, choose VESC as driver. Default CAN bus speed matches VESC default — no change needed. Check VESC status is OK and encoder rate is around 1000. When you move the wheel the bargraph must move.

That's the complete confirmed guide. The firmware file is **VESC_default.bin** from your already-downloaded Vesc4OpenFFBoard_410_o_411_o_412 folder, flashed via VESC Tool.

