Good question to nail down before writing anything.

**vJoy creates a virtual USB HID device on your PC.** The game sees it as a real physical FFB wheel plugged into USB.

It does two things simultaneously:

---

**Direction 1 — INPUT (phone → game)**
```
Phone gyro angle → PC receiver → writes to vJoy X axis → game reads steering position
```
Game sees: "wheel is turned 45° right"

---

**Direction 2 — OUTPUT (game → motor)**
```
Game calculates force → sends HID PID output report to vJoy →
PC receiver callback fires → reads force magnitude →
sends over COM to Uno → Uno sends setCurrent() to VESC → motor pushes back
```
Game sends: "apply 7000/10000 force to the left"

