- BeamNG ✅ (confirmed in SimWheel readme)
- Euro Truck Simulator 2 ✅
- AC EVO ❌ (blocks vJoy FFB)
- iRacing ⚠️ inconsistent

**vJoy is not a real USB device — it's a kernel driver that creates a virtual HID.** Games that check for real physical hardware will reject it. Games that just enumerate DirectInput devices will accept it.

---

So the answer to your question: USB HID is doing the FFB protocol translation between the game and your custom hardware. vJoy is the middleman.

Does the game you're planning to use actually support vJoy FFB? That determines whether this whole architecture works.

